Session of 2025
HOUSE BILL No. 2216
By Committee on Health and Human Services
Requested by Representative Bryce on behalf of Kansans for Life
2-3
1 AN ACT concerning health and healthcare; relating to abortion; requiring
2 the Kansas department of health and environment to create an
3 informational video describing abortion laws in Kansas and services
4 available for pregnant women experiencing life-threatening or health-
5 threatening medical conditions.
6
7 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
8 Section 1. (a) On or before September 1, 2025, the Kansas
9 department of health and environment shall create a video and other
10 materials that describe:
11 (1) The state's abortion laws, including acts that do or do not
12 constitute an abortion;
13 (2) the most common medical conditions that threaten the life or
14 health of a pregnant woman;
15 (3) the generally accepted standards of care applicable to the
16 treatment of a pregnant woman experiencing life-threatening or health-
17 threatening medical conditions; and
18 (4) the criteria that a practitioner, exercising reasonable medical
19 judgment, might use in determining the best course of treatment for a
20 pregnant woman and her unborn child who are experiencing life-
21 threatening or health-threatening medical conditions.
22 (b) In creating such video and other materials described in this
23 section, the department shall consult with the attorney general and persons
24 with medical and legal expertise.
25 (c) Upon completion of the requirements of subsections (a) and (b),
26 the department of health and environment shall make such video and
27 materials available on its website.
28 Sec. 2. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
29 publication in the statute book.

